Known issues

* The warnings 'unsafe code', 'unsafe type' and 'unsafe typecast' should be ignored
  when compiling the ExcelExport packages. In Delphi 7, 2005, 2006, Turbo Delphi,
  2007, 2009, 2010, XE, XE2, XE3, XE4, XE5, XE6, XE7, XE8, 10 (Seattle) and 10.1 (Berlin) these warnings can be disabled in your project options.
* EOleSysError "Class not registered" exception. This error occurs when one or more DLL's
  from Microsoft are not registered in Windows. You could register them with the
  regsvr.exe tool which can be found in Windows\System32 folder.
  The problem is that the EOleSysError does not specify which DLL's are causing the problem.
  So the best solution is to reinstall Office/Excel.
* Error reading ExplicitTop, ExplicitLeft, ExplicitWidth and ExplicitHeight properties when
  opening the demo application in other Delphi versions than 2007/2009/2010/XE/XE2/XE3/XE4/XE5/XE6/XE7/XE8/10/10.1
  Just choose "Ignore all". These properties will be removed from the DFM and
  the application will run fine in Delphi 6, 7, 2006, 2009, 2010, XE, XE2, XE3, XE4, XE5, XE6, XE7, XE8, 10 Seattle, 10.1 Berlin, ...
* The demo application uses the deprecated BDE database technology. The BDE is not included in XE10 anymore so you have
  to download it from http://cc.embarcadero.com/item/30359  
